<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> berserkers would like to see Aurora Borealis returned to &quot;after target parries.&quot; Along with this, it has been suggested that this style have a 6 or 9 second stun attached to it. The reasons for this are: it's our 50 spec style, and should, therefore, be quite powerful. Our only stun, which is 6 seconds off of Frosty Gaze, is very difficult for a berserker to land, while other classes are able to stun after an evade, from performing a simple positional style, or from hitting the button for 'Slam'. </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
-Or by performing a chain which stems off a parry. Get me?<br>
<br>
Parrying ones enemy is a positive assett. As Tundra penalises people for dual wielding, so Aurora Borealis would be (massively, massively) penalising people for having put more points into parry so they could stop being killed so often. All light tanks know what a 'slap in the face' is... A nine second stun to go along with this is the nail is anybody's coffin. Some classes rely on parrying. <br>
<br>
Change it to 'target evades' and I might look favourably upon it. And, if this sounds absurd, Dual Wield did actually have a style like this once.<br>
<br>
Increasing bleed damage to be on par with mercenaries Dual Shadows: of course I'll react with hostility towards what seems to be the only thing we've been given in a year that's of any worth. So forgive me. Dual Shadows bleed style is our level 50 style with an aggro-holding positional requirement and a medium defensive penalty, and poor bonus damage, yet a level 50 style should be <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em> &quot;quite powerful&quot; </em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> . The bleed upping was one of several tiny fixes that was supposed to make up for the fact that we don't do enough damage and never will.<br>
<br>
I'm horribly aware that it sounds like I'm being a bitch, but I feel I speak for more people than just myself.<br>
