<br>
No, you make good points.<br>
<br>
Also, my approach has always been to go with Mythic's definition of a light tank and to try to make the berserker fit that role and be useful/good at it, rather than being stubborn and insisting their idea of a Light Tank is wrong or bad.  The definition of a light tank, as per &quot;The Light Tank Explained,&quot; said that we shouldn't be able to go head to head with heavy tanks and win, and letting us stun off of Aurora Borealis would pretty much end the fight with any heavy tank that gets &quot;lucky&quot; enough to parry.  I spoke with the BM TL for awhile earlier, before reading your post, and this very point was made and I have to agree.  The last thing I want to do is contradict myself in my reports. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
&quot;<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>The bleed upping was one of several tiny fixes that was supposed to make up for the fact that we don't do enough damage and never will.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->&quot;<br>
<br>
Well, I honestly think that BMs and Mercenaries should have their damage increased.  Light tanks are supposed to do more damage than heavy tanks, but have weaker defense.  And if we're supposed to have &quot;much&quot; weaker defense, then we should have &quot;much&quot; stronger offense (note: I'm not saying Mythic has said this.  I'm just saying I think the adjectives should be the same in that comparison).<br>
<br>
Even before 1.62, I had a hard time beating warriors in duels because they would block and parry damn near everything.  In RvR, however, it was easier to win because parry didn't work.  Now that parry is fixed, heavy tanks are that much more defensive, and thus negate that much more of our offense in a head-on fight.  It's our job to attack them from different positions and to employ reactionary styles (or at least it's supposed to be), so it's my goal to get our reactionary and positional style damages increased, as well as get Left Axe a side positional and a good reactionary level 50 style, or at least something along those lines.<br>
<br>
I hope that BMs and Mercs get their damage increased, too.  None of us seem very good at being reactionary/positional fighters, so obviously something is wrong.<br>
<br>
 If your TLs ever need help with testing or anything else, I assure you I'll offer whatever I can to ensure that all of the light tanks function as they are supposed to.<br>
<br>
